<hl>
<seg id=1> According to Cotediwa Financial Minister, the economy in West Africa obviously returned to improve. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Abby, 18 January, by Hu Daocheng Cotediwa Financial Minister, Englan, said on 17 January that the economic situation in West Africa and countries of the Currency Association obviously returned to improve. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> On the economists' forum held in French Cotediwa Businessmen's Club Englan said that the average rate of economic increase in West Africa and countries of the Currency Association was 5.9% in 1996, 6.3% in 1997 and only 2.6% in 1994. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said that in recently years, West African countries improved the balance of import and export and the conditions for public investment. The favorable balance of trade increased quickly, and the estimated deficit obviously decreased, which was only 1.3% of the national output value. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> As far as that European Union's preparing to use the common currency would affect African franc was concerned, Englan believed that people would not worry about the future of African franc. </seg>
<seg id=6> He said that owing to economic improvement in West Africa and countries of the Currency Association, in a short time African franc would not devalue by 50% just like in 1994. </seg>
</p>
